{"word":"ὑπάγω","slug":"ὑπάγω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b><el>ὑπάγω</el></b> [<el><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:ὑπό\">ὑπό</a>, <a class=\"S\" href=\"S:ἄγω\">ἄγω</a></el>] in <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ NT\">NT</a> only <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ intr.\">intr.</a> ‘proceed from a position’<b><p class=\"pp3\"/>—<pp>a.</pp></b> <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ w.\">w.</a> focus on departure point <b>go away, leave <a href='B:470 4:10'>Mt 4:10</a>; <a href='B:470 16:23'>16:23</a>; <a href='B:470 19:21'>19:21</a>; <a href='B:480 5:34'>Mk 5:34</a>; <a href='B:480 8:33'>8:33</a>; <a href='B:500 6:67'>J 6:67</a>; <a href='B:660 2:16'>Js 2:16</a>.</b> As euphemism for dying <b><a href='B:470 26:24'>Mt 26:24</a>; <a href='B:480 14:21'>Mk 14:21</a>.—<a href='B:470 8:13'>Mt 8:13</a>; <a href='B:470 20:14'>20:14</a>; <a href='B:480 7:29'>Mk 7:29</a>; <a href='B:480 10:52'>10:52</a>,</b> in which <el>ὕπαγε</el> conveys the sense go home, offer a bridge to<b><p class=\"pp3\"/>—<pp>b.</pp></b> <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ w.\">w.</a> focus on objective or destination <b>go, be on one’s way <a href='B:470 5:24'>Mt 5:24</a>; <a href='B:470 8:4'>8:4</a>; <a href='B:470 9:6'>9:6</a>; <a href='B:470 13:44'>13:44</a>; <a href='B:470 18:15'>18:15</a>; <a href='B:480 11:2'>Mk 11:2</a>; <a href='B:490 8:42'>Lk 8:42</a>; <a href='B:500 3:8'>J 3:8</a>; <a href='B:500 9:7'>9:7</a>; <a href='B:690 2:11'>1 J 2:11</a>; <a href='B:730 10:8'>Rv 10:8</a>.</b> Of Jesus and his going to the Father <b><a href='B:500 7:33'>J 7:33</a></b> and oft in J. <center id=\"nav_bottom\"> <a id=\"left_arrow\" href=\"S:ὕμνος\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> <a id=\"bottom_home\" href=\"S:#1.Table of Contents\">&emsp;&emsp;</a> <a id=\"right_arrow\" href=\"S:ὑπακοή\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> </center> "}]}